<h2>FAQ</h2>
<h3>Who can participate?</h3>
<p>High school students in the United States, including rising 9th graders, with at least some previous iOS development experience.</p>
<p>The ideal candidate considers development as one of their primary hobbies and has built
  at least one app from the ground up.
</p>

<h3>How do I apply?</h3>
<p>Complete the <a href="/how-to-apply#challenge">challenge</a>, come up with a project idea, then fill out the <a href="/apply">application</a>.
<p>If we select your application for further consideration, we may contact you for a brief Skype/Google Hangout interview.</li>

<h3>How well do I have know iOS?</h3>
<p>Previous cadets have built at least one iOS app from the ground up, in Objective-C.</p>
<p>Not sure if you qualify? Try the <a href="/how-to-apply#challenge">challenge</a> and <a href="/apply">apply</a>! Even if you aren't
  accepted, you'll learn a lot in the process!
</p>

<h3>Where will be Afterburner be held?</h3>
<p>Online! No traveling required! All you need is a <a href="http://github.com">GitHub</a> account.</p>

<h3>How do I become a mentor?</h3>
<p>Email us at <a href="mailto:info@afterburner.me">info@afterburner.me</a></p>
